It is in principle straightforward to compute the higher order corrections to the
leading order result (). To find a sensible total production rate, however,
one would need to treat the probe quantum mechanically, so that the recoil is included
and total energy is preserved. It is evident from the matrix description that
all the initial energy (of order ) of the D-particle will be emitted in
the form of closed string tachyon radiation.






Large  RG Formulation of the Duality 

The matrix model
description in section 4 of  D-particles in 1+1-d string theory reveals a
universal behavior that depends only on one parameter: the
effective string coupling  (which e.g. sets both the size of the
tunneling amplitude ()) as well as of the eigenvalue density
 as given in ()). The model itself, however,
has two parameters: the number of D-particles  (all assumed
to be in their lowest possible energy eigenstate), the (bare)
string coupling .
We are therefore led to conclude that there should be an
equivalence between 1+1-d string theories with different values of
, , but with the same values for :
 ( g_s, N
